cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MS, cs.MM 

This paper presents a novel approach for segmenting 3-D OCT scans using probabilistic modeling and variational inference. The method involves modeling the appearance of retinal layers and global shape variations of layer boundaries. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of probabilistic modeling and variational inference suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves medical imaging, which suggests that it may belong to the medical imaging (cs.MS) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
